      <button type="button" class="as-reset" id="asReset">Reset defaults</button>
    </div>
    <p class="as-lead">Set these first so the answer below rests on visible ground, not a blank guess. They are grounded and sourced; change any of them if your own expectation differs.</p>
    <div class="as-controls">
      <div class="as-control">
        <div class="as-control-label">Time horizon
          <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">How long you hold. Bitcoin is a long-term commitment; a long enough hold has historically absorbed even a surprise drawdown. The case is a long-horizon one.</span></span>
          <span class="as-control-val" id="asHorizonVal">10 years</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="asHorizon" class="as-range" min="1" max="30" step="1" aria-label="Time horizon in years">
        <p class="as-control-note">A long enough hold has historically overcome even a surprise drawdown. See <a href="/the-bitcoin-horizon">The Bitcoin Horizon</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="as-control as-control-growth">
        <div class="as-control-label">Bitcoin grows by
          <span class="as-control-val" id="asBtcModeVal">—</span>
        </div>
        <div class="as-seg as-seg-mini as-seg-even" id="asBtcMode">
          <button type="button" data-val="hold">Today&rsquo;s gap to trend persists<span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Bitcoin keeps its current position relative to the Power Law trend (about 0.44&times; today) and grows along with the trend from there. Conservative from a discount: it does not assume the gap to trend closes.</span></span></button>
          <button type="button" data-val="revert">Return to trend<span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Bitcoin converges back to its full Power Law trend by the end of the hold. The more optimistic reading, since today&rsquo;s price sits below trend.</span></span></button>
          <button type="button" data-val="flat">Flat rate<span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">A simple constant annual growth rate you set yourself, ignoring the Power Law curve. A manual override for a reader with their own expectation.</span></span></button>
        </div>
        <div class="as-flat-wrap" id="asFlatWrap" hidden>
          <input type="range" id="asFlatRate" class="as-range as-range-red" min="0" max="30" step="1" aria-label="Flat bitcoin rate">
          <span class="as-flat-val" id="asFlatRateVal">15%/yr</span>
        </div>
        <p class="as-control-note">Projected from the Power Law, regime-aware. See <a href="/bull-and-bear-cycles">Bull &amp; Bear Cycles</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="as-control">
        <div class="as-control-label">The rest grows by
          <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Your broad-market sleeve. Default about 10%/yr, roughly the S&amp;P&rsquo;s long-run nominal return. Lower it toward 7% for a more conservative, real-terms figure.</span></span>
          <span class="as-control-val" id="asTradRateVal">10%/yr → 2.59x</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="asTradRate" class="as-range" min="0" max="15" step="1" aria-label="Traditional sleeve annual rate">
        <p class="as-control-note">Roughly the S&amp;P&rsquo;s long-run nominal return. The baseline bitcoin is measured against.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="as-control">
        <div class="as-control-label">Bad case: crash depth
          <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">How far bitcoin falls peak-to-trough in a bear market, for the drawdown figure. Bitcoin&rsquo;s bears have been getting shallower as it matures; −40% is a reasonable modern default, and deeper is available to stress-test.</span></span>
          <span class="as-control-val" id="asDepthVal">&minus;40%</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="asDepthSlider" class="as-range as-range-red" min="20" max="90" step="1" aria-label="Crash depth percent">
        <div class="as-seg as-seg-mini" id="asDepth">
          <button type="button" data-val="40">&minus;40%</button>
          <button type="button" data-val="60">&minus;60%</button>
          <button type="button" data-val="77">&minus;77%</button>
        </div>
        <p class="as-control-note">Bitcoin&rsquo;s bears have been getting shallower as it matures. Deeper is there to stress-test. See <a href="/bull-and-bear-cycles">Bull &amp; Bear Cycles</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="as-control">
        <div class="as-field">
          <span>Total portfolio (optional)
            <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Enter a dollar amount to see the extra return and the drawdown as real dollars. Leave blank to stay in multiples and percentages.</span></span>
          </span>
          <input type="text" inputmode="numeric" id="asPortfolio" placeholder="e.g. 500,000" aria-label="Total portfolio in dollars">
